verbs.description: inweave (third-person singular simple present inweaves, present participle inweaving, simple past inwove or inweaved, past participle inwoven or inweaved)

entries.meaning: (archaic, literary) To weave in or together; to intermix or intertwine by weaving; to interlace.
examples: [The enchanted standard] contained the figure of a raven, which had been inwove by the three sisters of Hinguar and Hubba with many magical incantations  […]
